.\" heirloom-port-install(7)
.TH HEIRLOOM-PORT-INSTALL 7 "2026-07-02" "Heirloom Darwin port" "Port ALM"
.SH NAME
heirloom-port-install \- install the port under a prefix + record a manifest
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B make install
.RI "[" "PREFIX=/some/where" "] [" "ROOT=/staging" "]"
.SH DESCRIPTION
Delegates to the upstream
.I makefile
.B install
target with
.BR ROOT= " and " PREFIX=
propagated. On completion,
.I scripts/write-manifest.sh
enumerates the files placed under
.I ROOT/PREFIX
and writes them to
.I .install-manifest-\fIpkg\fP.txt
at the repo root. The manifest is consumed by
.BR heirloom-port-uninstall (7).
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B PREFIX
Install prefix. Default
.IR /opt/heirloom .
.TP
.B ROOT
DESTDIR-style staging root. Default empty (install directly).
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Install directly into /opt/heirloom:
.B make install
.TP
Stage into a tarball root:
.B make install ROOT=/tmp/pkgroot
.SH FILES
.TP
.I .install-manifest-\fIpkg\fP.txt
List of every file + symlink created under
.IR PREFIX ,
one path per line. Kept in the repo root for audit; consumed by
.BR heirloom-port-uninstall (7).
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR heirloom-port-uninstall (7),
.BR heirloom-port-verify (7),
.BR heirloom-port-status (7)
